{"name":"Faction Defender","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This character is a well-known member of her faction and they’re more willing to help her out in time of need than most.<p>Favors (see page 34) cost one point less with members of the Ripper’s faction—to a minimum of one.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 19","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 19","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"S, Persuasion d6, Status 3"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_xn38iet471","path":"Rippers Resurrected","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.PAFgtFYgIZIXUhK9"}},"_id":"mIkZ5B1UZyIinEkq"}
{"name":"White Eagle Military Contracting","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Members of the WEMC gain the Rock & Roll Edge when fighting alongside allies.","notes":"Monster Hunters International page 136","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Acceptance into the WEMC, Seasoned."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.monster-hunter-international.CrcwVlj4Ywklqj5Z"},"cf":{"id":"temp_rrxjx1x6f9k","path":"Monster Hunter International","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"oM4cEJaoZKXS4irX"}
{"name":"Uwharrie Special Security Services","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"USSS has a depth of knowledge related to occult lore due to their founder being a rare book dealer. They gain +2 to Occult and Academics rolls.","notes":"Monster Hunters International page 136","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Acceptance into USSS."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.monster-hunter-international.Bm9vX77XGzWVk2Jf"},"cf":{"id":"temp_rrxjx1x6f9k","path":"Monster Hunter International","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"oq6UjqfNF2CI4jJR"}
{"name":"Sound Mind","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This investigator has learned to cope with the terrors he must face and the dark things that lurk in his world. Increase his Sanity by +2.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Horror Companion, page 6","notes":"Horror Companion, page 6","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_fds2de065xm","path":"Horror Companion","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.yfmD2r0KworOzXnp"}},"_id":"pHkUesUV1J6d7Zgg"}
{"name":"Alternate Identity","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your Ripper has another identity she can assume. The identity must be of lower Status than her own, and when assumed, incurs the relevant modifiers and station as usual.<p>People who know the individual in one identity and encounter the other make a Notice roll at –4, opposed by Stealth, to determine the truth. People who are more intimately familiar may suffer a reduced penalty, or none at all, at the Game Master’s discretion.<p>Scandals that affect the alter ego don’t affect the real individual. Also, since certain eccentricities are expected of such do-gooders, covering up Scandals (see page 34) costs one less Favor than usual.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 19","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 19","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Performance d6"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_xn38iet471","path":"Rippers Resurrected","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.SbI5rmok5lHU2YAe"}},"_id":"pyjpFRVY5KQurbeN"}
{"name":"The Heracles Foundation","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"All members of the HF gain +2 on all Soak rolls, and the Overconfident Hindrance. They tend to take after their namesake in subtle ways.","notes":"Monster Hunters International page 136","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Acceptance into the HF"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.monster-hunter-international.qYbfFkH3lkxxF01l"},"cf":{"id":"temp_rrxjx1x6f9k","path":"Monster Hunter International","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"qoQY7lp2rbE78CxD"}
{"name":"Cairo Paranormal Investigations","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Members of Cairo PI are adept at investigation, subterfuge and intrigue. They gain +2 to all Persuasion rolls when in disguise or acting, and can spend a Benny to gain entrance to any location they wish (GM’s discretion. Some hyper-secure facilities might be too far, even for Cairo PI.)","notes":"Monster Hunters International page 134","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Acceptance into the Cairo PI."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.monster-hunter-international.BL8rcC0JkFDJS4sZ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_rrxjx1x6f9k","path":"Monster Hunter International","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"qw19T0i6cwgN8zd0"}
{"name":"Fortune Favors the Bold","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Explorers, cowboys, tomb raiders, and hired guns like Frazer’s Fighters fight creatures of darkness like all Rippers, but crave action and adventure (and sometimes treasure!) more than most other crusaders.<p>Fortune favors the bold, it is said, and those who go through secret initiations (similar to Masonic rituals) at their headquarters in Cairo are particularly blessed. The hero starts each session with one extra Benny (even if an Extra). This likely explains why so many of Frazer’s Fighters survive encounters and stunts others do not.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 16","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 16","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Faction (Frazer's Fighters)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_xn38iet471","path":"Rippers Resurrected","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.TVytAvupCS4kx5rr"}},"_id":"t3QwKV7HNFGVR2DH"}
{"name":"Sterner Stuff","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"When this hero has rippertech implanted, the surgeon gains a +2 bonus to his Knowledge (Rippertech) roll due to the subject’s phenomenal constitution, raw willpower, or fierce determination.<p>In addition, the Ripper adds +2 to all Vigor rolls required when using extractions (including attempting to use multiple concoctions (see <b>Using Extracts,</b> page 47).</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 16","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 16","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, V d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_xn38iet471","path":"Rippers Resurrected","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.H8XGEGTaDNfkvQ7Z"}},"_id":"tpsx8hDfrzmOWGew"}
{"name":"Witch/Warlock","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"There are plenty of good witches and warlocks out there. Hopefully, this hero remains one of them.</p><p> When casting a ritual (by the time you’re a Junior you’ll know what they are), she ignores up to 2 points of Casting Modifiers. This does not apply to other participants, who still roll with the usual penalties.","notes":"East Texas University page 17","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Junior"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.east-texas-university.7I41rF0nxDWvauRm"},"cf":{"id":"temp_cvxwaokd0ri","path":"East Texas University","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"u5V7cs9GUjoZS6vg"}
{"name":"Cascade Crushers","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Cascade Crushers were founded by a former SWAT officer and detective. They’ve got some of the best training when it comes to combining modern police work with monster hunting.</p><p>When making Research rolls related to monsters, Cascade Crushers gain +2 to the roll.","notes":"Monster Hunters International page 134","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Acceptance into the Cascade Crushers."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.monster-hunter-international.ApHkqyXHxjCa0k1L"},"cf":{"id":"temp_rrxjx1x6f9k","path":"Monster Hunter International","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"udTwWrLXKjyLU7gT"}
{"name":"Devout","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Devout students believe in a greater power, deity, or spirit, or perhaps just their own sense of self and willpower. They are typically religious, but don’t have to be. Devout heroes add +2 to all opposed Spirit rolls where their faith might come into play such as resisting evil powers (Dean’s call).","notes":"East Texas University page 16","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Freshman, Spirit d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.east-texas-university.y46lgc1Ev8f7vcwp"},"cf":{"id":"temp_cvxwaokd0ri","path":"East Texas University","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"vQSUIzFYFrIVDRNn"}
{"name":"Aura Reader","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"This Edge allows the student to read another person’s energy—or “aura.”</p><p> To do so, the character must be within ten feet (in person—video doesn’t work) and make a Spirit roll at –2. If the roll is successful, the character knows the target’s general emotional state (happy, sad, angry, nervous, etc.) and her overall health (sick, weak, strong, etc.). With a raise, she can identify specific health conditions, such as a concussion, spirit possession, Fatigue, cancer, diabetes, etc. Failure results in a level of Fatigue and loss of the ability for 24 hours.","notes":"East Texas University page 17","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Sophomore, Psychically Sensitive, Spirit d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.east-texas-university.BfC4aJNBFaISy4Us"},"cf":{"id":"temp_cvxwaokd0ri","path":"East Texas University","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"vkrTsEJfHq3m0ACX"}
{"name":"Down-to-Earth","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Your hero is of sound mind and not prone to flights of fancy. Although the supernatural is still frightening, he or she has the good sense to remain rooted in reality. A character with this Edge is more likely to be able to deal with the many horrors of the Cabal and can better resist rippertech’s harmful effects. Modify this hero’s Reason by +1.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 16","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 16","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Sp d8"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_xn38iet471","path":"Rippers Resurrected","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.kARGTEGbUa8Uya9L"}},"_id":"wD2mZ6woGdDPEj4l"}
{"name":"Charms & Wards","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Witch hunters spend their days tracking down witches, hags, and rogue priests, and know how to prepare certain minor charms, tattoos, symbols, and even odors or ointments to ward off their evil eyes.<p>Black magic (and Special Abilities that mimic such power) used against the hero suffers a –2 penalty to the arcane skill roll.</p><p><b>Source: </b>Rippers Resurrected, page 16","notes":"Rippers Resurrected, page 16","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"N, Faction (Witch Hunter)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_xn38iet471","path":"Rippers Resurrected","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.jd-weird-world.jd-weird-world-edges.lhBjTB5tYmPTmE1W"}},"_id":"yyurvt3FQ8Putzba"}
{"name":"Chosen One","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"Various forces of the cosmos often choose champions to serve them. Once per session a Chosen One may ignore a wound that would move them to Incapacitated. After they do so, they gain one Benny. Being a Champion of the universe is risky business, and a lot of folks will want you deader than dead. Therefore, each Chosen One also gains the Enemy (Major) Hinderance. This Enemy is an opposed faction to the faction that selected the Chosen One.","notes":"Monster Hunters International page 134","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"None"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.monster-hunter-international.C4EqmbUBLJbrHdEt"},"cf":{"id":"temp_rrxjx1x6f9k","path":"Monster Hunter International","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"yzURB0i4Sx5S3lrU"}
{"name":"Sonderjagdkommandos","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"SJK members gain +1 on attack and damage rolls against Vampires. They’re very good at killing Vampires.","notes":"Monster Hunters International page 135","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Acceptance into the SJK"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"UeH4lLk57wAOn2HV":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.monster-hunter-international.SlkR6AsWD9DZTZ1n"},"cf":{"id":"temp_rrxjx1x6f9k","path":"Monster Hunter International","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"zeCcvYM29174FPIS"}
